event.title: Disney Xmas Classics : Aladdin
event.description:
A highly entertaining entry in Disney's renaissance era," Aladdin is beautifully drawn, with near-classic songs and a cast of scene-stealing characters.

 

Robin Williams's dizzying and hilarious voicing of the Genie is the main attraction of Aladdin, the third in the series of modern Disney animated movies that began with 1989's The Little Mermaid and heralded a new age for the genre. After a sultan (Douglas Seale) gives his daughter, Jasmine (Linda Larkin), three days to find a husband, she escapes the palace and encounters the street-savvy urchin Aladdin (Scott Weinger), who charms his way into her heart. While the sultan's Vizier, Jafar (Jonathan Freeman), weaves a spell so that he may marry Jasmine and become sultan himself, Aladdin discovers the Genie's lamp in a cave, rubs it, and sets the mystical entity free, leading the Genie to pledge his undying loyalty to the dazzled youth. Aladdin begins his quest to defeat Jafar and win the hand of the princess, with the Genie's help. Monsters, Disney's trademark talking animals, and a flying carpet all figure into the ensuing adventures, but Williams' Genie, who can change into anything or anybody, steals the show as he launches into one crazed monologue after another, impersonating figures from Ed Sullivan to Elvis Presley.

event.title: UK Foo Flighters 10th Anniversary Tour
event.description: This gig is at the Academy Green Room in Dublin. Doors open 7:00pm on Sat 16 Dec 2017 The Academy is one of Dublin’s busiest concert venues. With its three rooms within the same building (Main Room, Academy 2and The Green Room), The Academy is hosting a show almost every night. Located in Dublin City centre, just a few minutes walk from O’Connell street, The Academy is easily accessible, whether you’re going by bus, Luas, DART, bike or by foot. When Jay formed this tribute act in 2006 he never dreamed he would be paying homage to what would become one of rock’s legendary bands. Jay and the rest of his UK Foo Fighters (Arron, Alex & Jamie) have performed at numerous festivals, corporate events, weddings, private parties and even ‘Garage Tour’ stops (just like the Foos) across the UK and Europe, sharing bills with acts such as Feeder and BBC Radio One DJ Zane Lowe. At every turn Jay has not only questioned the point/purpose of his tribute band but particularly, his own ability to emulate a front man with as much charisma and energy on stage as Dave Grohl. What truly drives his passion today is the music and performing live. That coupled with the overwhelming feedback he receives following every performance. See more info at ukfoofighterstribute.co.uk UK Foo Fighters Tribute tour dates listed on Ents24.com since Jun 2007. These tickets are strictly for over 18's.
